This paper focuses on improving the interpretability of LDA topic models through analyzing and visualizing their outputs. The paper specifically discusses the use of topic similarity networks, which are graphs that represent latent topics in text collections and their similarities. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), social and information networks (cs.SI), deep learning (cs.DL), and machine learning (cs.LG).
